==Ethnicity==
'''Nationality:'''
* ''noun:'' [[Canadians|Canadian]](s)
* ''adjective:'' Canadian

===Ethnic origin===
{{Main|Ethnic origins of people in Canada}}
Canadians were able to self-identify one or more ethnic origins in the [[Canada 2006 Census|2006 census]]. Percentages may therefore add up to more than 100%. The most common response was 'Canadian'. As data is completely self-reported, and reporting individuals may have varying definitions of &quot;Ethnic origin&quot; (or may not know their ethnic origin), these figures should not be considered an exact record of the relative prevalence of different ethnocultural ancestries.

Statistics Canada projects that, by 2031, approximately 28% of the population will be foreign-born. The number of people belonging to [[visible minority]] groups will double,&lt;ref&gt;
{{cite web
|url=http://www.ctv.ca/servlet/ArticleNews/story/CTVNews/20100314/Minority_Report_100314/20100314?hub=Canada
|title=Parties prepare to battle for Immigrant votes|publisher=[[CTV.ca]]|accessdate=2010-03-15|date=2010-03-14}}
&lt;/ref&gt;
and make up the majority of the population in Toronto and Vancouver.

'''Single responses:''' 18.40% of respondents gave a single response of 'Canadian', while a further 13.82% identified with both 'Canadian', and one or more other ancestries. 4.38% of respondents gave a single response of [[English people|English]], 3.94% gave a single response of [[French people|French]], 3.63% gave a single response of [[Chinese people|Chinese]], 2.50% gave a single response of [[Demographics of India|East Indian]], 2.37% gave a single response of [[Italian people|Italian]], 2.15% gave a single response of [[Germans|German]], 1.82% gave a single response of [[Scottish people|Scottish]], 1.64% gave a single response of [[First Nations|North American Indian]], 1.57% gave a single response of [[Irish people|Irish]], and 1.03% gave a single response of [[Filipino people|Filipino]].

'''Multiple responses:''' Counting both single and multiple responses, the most commonly identified ethnic origins were (2006):
{| class=&quot;wikitable sortable&quot; style=&quot;margin:left&quot;
