==Diplomatic missions==
===Canadian missions in the United States===
[[File:Embassy of Canada in Washington, D.C..JPG|thumb|[[Canadian Embassy, Washington, D.C.|Embassy of Canada]] in Washington, D.C.]]
Canada's chief diplomatic mission to the United States is the Canadian Embassy in [[Washington, D.C.]]. It is further supported by many Consulates located through United States of America.&lt;ref&gt;{{cite web|url=http://www.canadainternational.gc.ca/boston/offices-bureaux/index.aspx?lang=eng&amp;menu_id=179&amp;menu=L |title=Canadian Government offices in the U.S |publisher=Canadainternational.gc.ca |date=2009-02-26 |accessdate=2011-02-26}}&lt;/ref&gt;
The Canadian Government supports Consulates in several major U.S. cities including: [[Anchorage, Alaska|Anchorage]], [[Atlanta, Georgia|Atlanta]]&lt;sup&gt;‡&lt;/sup&gt;, [[Boston]]&lt;sup&gt;‡&lt;/sup&gt;, [[Buffalo, New York|Buffalo]]&lt;sup&gt;‡&lt;/sup&gt;, [[Chicago, Illinois|Chicago]]&lt;sup&gt;‡&lt;/sup&gt;, [[Dallas, Texas|Dallas]]&lt;sup&gt;‡&lt;/sup&gt;, [[Denver, Colorado|Denver]]&lt;sup&gt;‡&lt;/sup&gt;, [[Detroit, Michigan|Detroit]]&lt;sup&gt;‡&lt;/sup&gt;, [[Houston, Texas|Houston]], [[Los Angeles, California|Los Angeles]]&lt;sup&gt;‡&lt;/sup&gt;, [[Miami, Florida|Miami]]&lt;sup&gt;‡&lt;/sup&gt;, [[Minneapolis, Minnesota|Minneapolis]]&lt;sup&gt;‡&lt;/sup&gt;, [[New York City, New York|New York City]]&lt;sup&gt;‡&lt;/sup&gt;, [[Philadelphia, Pennsylvania|Philadelphia]], [[Phoenix, Arizona|Phoenix]], [[Raleigh, North Carolina|Raleigh]], [[San Diego, California|San Diego]], [[San Francisco, California|San Francisco]]/[[Silicon Valley, California|Silicon Valley]]&lt;sup&gt;‡&lt;/sup&gt;, [[Sacramento, California|Sacramento]], and [[Seattle, Washington|Seattle]]&lt;sup&gt;‡&lt;/sup&gt;
*‡ ''denotes mission is [[Consulate#Consulates and embassies|Consul General]]''

There are also trade offices located in [[Princeton, New Jersey|Princeton]] and [[Palo Alto, California|Palo Alto]]

===American missions in Canada===
The United States's chief diplomatic mission to Canada is the United States Embassy in [[Ottawa]]. It is further supported by many consulates located through Canada.&lt;ref&gt;{{cite web|url=http://canada.usembassy.gov/ |title=American Government offices in Canada |publisher=Canada.usembassy.gov |date= |accessdate=2011-02-26}}&lt;/ref&gt;
The American government supports consulates in several major Canadian cities/regions including:
[[Calgary]], [[Halifax Regional Municipality|Halifax]], [[Northwest Territories]]&lt;sup&gt;‡&lt;/sup&gt;, [[Nunavut]]&lt;sup&gt;‡&lt;/sup&gt;, [[Montreal]], [[Quebec City]], [[Southwestern Ontario]]&lt;sup&gt;‡&lt;/sup&gt;, [[Toronto]], [[Vancouver]], [[Winnipeg]], and [[Yukon]]&lt;sup&gt;‡&lt;/sup&gt;.
* ‡ ''denotes mission is a Virtual Presence Post (VPP)''

